flowchart TD
    A([Change Request]) --> B{Emergency?}
    B --> |Yes| C[Emergency CAB]
    B --> |No| D[Standard Review]
    C --> E[Expedited Approval]
    D --> F[Weekly CAB Meeting]
    F --> G{Approved?}
    G --> |Yes| H[Schedule Change Window]
    G --> |No| I[Return to Requester]
    H --> J[Implementation]
    J --> K{Successful?}
    K --> |Yes| L[Post-Impl Review]
    %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION
    K --> |No| M1[Execute Backout Plan]
    M1 --> M2{Backout Successful?}
    M2 --> |Yes| M3[Document Backout & Lessons Learned]
    M2 --> |No| M[Incident Report]
    M3 --> I
    %% ⚡ END CHANGED SECTION
    L --> N([Close Change])
    M --> N

%% ========================================================
%% CLAUDE'S CHANGE INTERPRETATION
%% ========================================================
%% OBJECTIVE: Ensure failed implementations follow a structured rollback process before escalating to incident management, minimizing service disruption during change windows.
%%
%% EXPLANATION:
%% Replaced the direct path from implementation failure to Incident Report with a backout plan workflow. When implementation fails, the process now first executes the backout plan, then checks if the backout was successful. If the backout succeeds, the change is documented with lessons learned and returned to the requester for rework. If the backout itself fails, an Incident Report is created as before, escalating the issue appropriately.
%% ========================================================
